      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SHE'S GOT THE CASH (10) finished third when resuming from a spell last start over 1415m at Sale after she made late ground. Was beaten only 1.7 lengths by the handy Fatty Finn that day and it's doubtful any rivals here would be capable of doing that. The step up to 1600m looks perfect second-up. CHRONIC (2) finished second over 1400m at Sale two back then missed the frame last time out over 1429m at Sale. Should be nearing peak fitness now and couldn't have hoped to find a better race to strike back. MISS XTRAVAGANZA (7) settled well back then made some inroads and finished 5 lengths away in sixth last time out over 1312m at Geelong two weeks ago. Extra trip here suits. DOWNTHERABBITHOLE (6) was never really in the hunt last time, drifting back early and winding up 6 lengths from the winner in fifth over 1600m at Cranbourne. Draws well and gets her best chance in a while at a second career placing.",
